    {
      "id": "template-structure-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Template / Structure Nodeset",
      "position": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": -430
      },
      "width": 500,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Template / Structure Nodeset\n\nCandidate types for a reusable template-structure family:\n- `title`\n- `section`\n- `slot`\n- `instruction`\n- `example`\n- `constraint`\n\nDeferred or boundary candidates:\n- `subtitle`\n- `variant`\n- `default`\n- `note`\n\nThis family matters if Twilite wants good graphs to be easier to author through reusable structure instead of only through freeform markdown and ad hoc graph shape.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
